.TH "mii_check_media" 9 "mii_check_media" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mii_check_media \- check the MII interface for a carrier/speed/duplex change
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" mii_check_media
.BI "(struct mii_if_info *mii "  ","
.BI "unsigned int ok_to_print "  ","
.BI "unsigned int init_media "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mii" 12
the MII interface
.IP "ok_to_print" 12
OK to print link up/down messages
.IP "init_media" 12
OK to save duplex mode in \fImii\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 1 if the duplex mode changed, 0 if not.
If the media type is forced, always returns 0.
